subject: Merge tag 'scsi-fixes' of git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/jejb/scsi
body:
Pull SCSI fixes from James Bottomley:
 "Two iscsi fixes.

  One for an oops in the client which can be triggered by the server
  authentication protocol and the other in the target code which causes
  data corruption"

* tag 'scsi-fixes' of git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/jejb/scsi:
  scsi: iscsi: set auth_protocol back to NULL if CHAP_A value is not supported
  scsi: target/iblock: Fix overrun in WRITE SAME emulation
full_message:
Merge tag 'scsi-fixes' of git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/jejb/scsi

Pull SCSI fixes from James Bottomley:
 "Two iscsi fixes.

  One for an oops in the client which can be triggered by the server
  authentication protocol and the other in the target code which causes
  data corruption"

* tag 'scsi-fixes' of git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/jejb/scsi:
  scsi: iscsi: set auth_protocol back to NULL if CHAP_A value is not supported
  scsi: target/iblock: Fix overrun in WRITE SAME emulation
